As per the forecast by the regional met department, heat wave conditions are likely to prevail in isolated pockets of several districts of Maharashtra on Thursday. Districts including Sangli, Sholapur, Sambhajinagar, Jalna, Parbhani, Hingoli, Akola, Amravati and Wardha will experience this.
{{/usCountry}}
{{#usCountry}}
As per the forecast by the regional met department, heat wave conditions are likely to prevail in isolated pockets of several districts of Maharashtra on Thursday. Districts including Sangli, Sholapur, Sambhajinagar, Jalna, Parbhani, Hingoli, Akola, Amravati and Wardha will experience this.
IMD said that there will be a rise in the maximum temperature by 1-2 degrees Celcius over parts of Maharashtra till April 18 and a gradual fall by 2-3 degrees thereafter.
